SSM6515 I2C Audio Amplifier Driver
devices

Detailed Description

Purpose: This module provides a comprehensive hardware abstraction layer for the Analog Devices SSM6515 digital audio amplifier. The driver enables high-performance audio playback with extensive configuration options through I2C control interface. It supports wide sample rate ranges, multiple audio interface modes, power management, and gain control. Configuration tables are generated using Analog Devices' SigmaStudio tool for optimal audio performance and system integration.

Key Features

  1. High-Performance Audio Amplification: Digital Class-D amplifier with superior audio quality.
  2. Wide Sample Rate Support: 8kHz to 768kHz sample rates for diverse audio applications.
  3. Flexible Audio Interfaces: Stereo and TDM (Time Division Multiplexing) modes.
  4. TDM Slot Configuration: 16-bit, 24-bit, and 32-bit slot width support.
  5. Programmable Gain Control: Software-controlled volume adjustment.
  6. Power Management: Software power up/down control for energy efficiency.
  7. SigmaStudio Integration: Uses configuration tables generated by SigmaStudio tool.
  8. I2C Interface: Standard I2C communication for control and configuration.

Functionality

  • Initialize and configure SSM6515 amplifier via I2C interface
  • Configure wide range of audio sample rates (8kHz to 768kHz)
  • Set audio interface mode (Stereo I2S or TDM)
  • Configure TDM slot width for multi-channel audio systems
  • Control amplifier gain for volume adjustment
  • Manage power states for optimal energy consumption
  • Load SigmaStudio-generated configuration tables
  • Handle register-level configuration with read/write operations
  • Support full reset and initialization sequences

Usage

  1. Initialize I2C interface with am_devices_ssm6515_i2c_init()
  2. Initialize SSM6515 device with am_devices_ssm6515_init()
  3. Configure sample rate with am_devices_ssm6515_set_sample_rate()
  4. Set audio interface mode with am_devices_ssm6515_set_sai_mode()
  5. Configure TDM parameters with am_devices_ssm6515_set_tdm_slot_width()
  6. Adjust gain with am_devices_ssm6515_set_gain()
  7. Control power state with am_devices_ssm6515_power_down()
  8. Play audio through configured amplifier
  9. Deinitialize device with am_devices_ssm6515_deinit()
  10. Deinitialize I2C interface with am_devices_ssm6515_i2c_deinit()

Configuration

  • Set up I2C interface parameters and timing
  • Configure audio sample rates based on system requirements
  • Set up audio interface mode (Stereo vs TDM) for system topology
  • Configure TDM slot parameters for multi-channel audio
  • Load SigmaStudio-generated configuration tables
  • Set up gain control ranges and behavior
  • Configure power management for optimal efficiency
  • Optimize register settings for specific audio applications
